        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 7:13PM CDT by NWS Grand Forks ND</headline>
        <description>At 712 PM CDT, trained weather spotters reported a strong
thunderstorm over Marcoux, or 25 miles south of Thief River Falls,
moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Trained weather spotters.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Erskine, Mentor, Dugdale, and Marcoux.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
northwestern Minnesota.</instruction>
